Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.28,0:00:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, I've talked to Dr. Hawkins, and I can tell you he's in rare form.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.71,0:00:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So put your hands together and welcome again our mentor and teacher, Dr. David Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.64,0:01:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll see, according to the schedule, what is today called?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.85,0:01:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.68,0:01:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Traditional dialogue between teachers and students.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.40,0:01:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what we'll do today primarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.96,0:01:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We, of course, have new slides, which we promise not to subject you to today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.23,0:01:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Exciting new developments, because the consciousness research just keeps pulling up amazing information
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.50,0:01:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it all correlates is rather staggering.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.03,0:01:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll control myself and try not to show you a new slide that's just mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.01,0:02:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We might show them one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.62,0:02:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We might show them one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.37,0:02:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The one I'm holding in mind is okay to show them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.00,0:02:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.78,0:02:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we're going to do it a little differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.55,0:02:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go up here and we're going to discuss things in greater detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.52,0:02:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All the questions that, of course, now wonderful season.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.53,0:02:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All these flowers seem to indicate something coming up in a couple of weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.00,0:02:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,which we will avoid mentioning in public, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.56,0:02:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sort of a special day that comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.80,0:03:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,One of a number of special days.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.81,0:03:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, we're the only secular spiritual group on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.71,0:03:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I mentioned no religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.88,0:03:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stick to the Rhapsody of the Soul stunningly, it doesn't represent any particular religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.15,0:04:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't represent any school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.94,0:04:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It teaches stunningly, starkly, totality of all, the source of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.38,0:04:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Its nature shines forth from all that exists and makes it difficult to function in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.36,0:04:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,so we won't talk about it too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.68,0:04:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, the lecture will come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.70,0:04:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not necessary to get caught in the trappings of tradition
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.85,0:04:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,with all of the incrustation that has occurred to it over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.64,0:04:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It starts out as some kind of a purity,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.17,0:04:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,radiating forth from someone who has realized the presence of God is the source of all existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.45,0:04:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and then it becomes institutionalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.89,0:05:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And within the institutionalization, then it becomes encrusted and rigid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.76,0:05:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Sultifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.37,0:05:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And then people are brought up in it as children,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.93,0:05:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and they become antagonistic to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.07,0:05:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and don't want to hear about it again,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.27,0:05:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and become champions of the opposite of truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.60,0:05:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,having been disillusioned or suffered some kind of discomfort
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.57,0:05:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,due to the way in which it was presented to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.06,0:05:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They avoid it altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.29,0:05:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, we can say truthfully,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.82,0:05:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we are the only secular spiritual group that I know of.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.05,0:05:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth needs no external authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.77,0:05:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth speaks for itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.54,0:05:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The devotion to truth is the devotion to the essence of the source of all existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.25,0:06:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,which in some quarters and historically has been called God.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.06,0:06:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree with the Buddha it's better not to mention such a word,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.39,0:06:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has become imbued with so many meanings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.50,0:06:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So many meanings that there's opposition to its use in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.86,0:06:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And so many meanings that there's opposition to its use in.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.31,0:06:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it seems to those people
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.18,0:06:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that it represents some kind of an oppression or loss of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.58,0:06:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which is the true source of freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.86,0:06:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,now becomes pictured as the enemy of freedom.
