Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.06,1:23:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,then the spirit lives on and accumulates this wisdom because that's the nature of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.30,1:23:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so if you segment off a personal spirit ego personal soul et cetera it partakes of the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.98,1:23:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,same quality of the nature of consciousness itself and also learns and grows over time
Dialogue: 0,1:23:26.98,1:23:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,over great periods of time, great eons of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.81,1:23:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we go in and out of body,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.64,1:23:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but the spirit remains the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.89,1:23:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So the spirit is accumulating a learningness,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.89,1:23:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a learningness over great expanses of time
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.93,1:23:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,until it becomes aware eventually
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.13,1:23:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of the source of its own existence and its own reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.93,1:23:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that challenge of giving up the palace
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.06,1:23:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably one of the greatest human challenges.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.01,1:23:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it goes back to my original question,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.40,1:23:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is when you get to that point,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.40,1:24:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that's a fairly advanced state of karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.09,1:24:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and it isn't wealth, it's the attachment to wealth.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.28,1:24:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because wealth is just a useful tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.81,1:24:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So to Einstein or any of those people,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.67,1:24:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,wealth was just a means of doing the necessary engineering.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.52,1:24:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So creativity was what they're committed to.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.77,1:24:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So the wealth of this nation is creativity itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.40,1:24:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it seems to be a society which potentiates, underlines,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.86,1:24:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and values individual creativity from Alexander Graham Bell to...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.64,1:24:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:41.64,1:24:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill Gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.64,1:24:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill Gates.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.64,1:24:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that his name?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.18,1:24:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.18,1:24:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Big Bill.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.18,1:24:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So see, all that comes out as an automatic consequence.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.18,1:24:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If you design an automobile to get you from one place to another,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.10,1:24:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the world throngs to it and wants more, so...
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.00,1:25:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My observation just comes from, like you're saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.07,1:25:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to get to my own enlightenment, not so much,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.07,1:25:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to understand money and that,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.73,1:25:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to understand the system in which I'm observing.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.84,1:25:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's as if I'm trying to gain compassion,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.30,1:25:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because I'm trying to look at everything with compassion.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.35,1:25:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is something I used to not look at with compassion,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.23,1:25:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so I can see the beauty and the struggle of that challenge
Dialogue: 0,1:25:19.43,1:25:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of the birthright to brilliance, like Gates, and brilliance and money,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:24.15,1:25:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fact that separation of money is one of the most challenging things.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:29.47,1:25:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a writer, someone who doesn't write for money,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.47,1:25:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to understand the system in which I'm observing.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.47,1:25:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone who doesn't write for money,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:33.30,1:25:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,someone who writes for the joy of being inside my head, inside my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:38.07,1:25:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why Gates enjoyed computers, but there's a byproduct of that of wealth.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.43,1:25:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the byproduct of the wealth in the human experience is,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.10,1:25:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you do with all of that power and be separated from it?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.67,1:25:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I wouldn't say wealth is power, wealth is convenience.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.67,1:25:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, grace, oil on the tracks, something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.51,1:26:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Society creates the wealth, the person doesn't create the wealth.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.43,1:26:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, how many of you know that?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.85,1:26:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How many automobiles did Henry Ford make?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.85,1:26:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He never made one, probably.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.85,1:26:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He just made the parts.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.85,1:26:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, society came in and demanded it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.85,1:26:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We want this thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.85,1:26:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then society provides the workers and the incentive.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.85,1:26:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And the banks, of course, you need to make money.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.85,1:26:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to create an automobile factory, you've got to make money from the banks to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.64,1:26:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So you could look at it as mutually beneficial to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.02,1:26:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.02,1:26:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.02,1:26:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see a capitalist and a worker as a perpetrator and victim at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.02,1:26:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That was Marx's great error, disaster's error.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.52,1:26:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he separated it that way, he doesn't see that everything is mutually beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.02,1:26:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the worker, the factory can't be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.10,1:26:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the factory, there's no way to build factories.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.68,1:26:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And without that, there's no capital.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.18,1:26:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Without that, there's no bank.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.18,1:26:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And without that, there's no grocery store.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.18,1:26:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And without that, the kid's still hungry.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.18,1:26:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I see the value in all of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.18,1:27:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I see sustainability.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.18,1:27:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I see sustainability.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.18,1:27:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I see society as mutually beneficial, a mutuality to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.18,1:27:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How you look at it, holographically.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.18,1:27:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,From this way, politics looks wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.47,1:27:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,From this way, politics looks, how could you live without it?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.47,1:27:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,From this way, capital looks wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.47,1:27:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,From this way, what would you wear today without the rich capitalist pigs?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.97,1:27:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.97,1:27:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have to sew your own clothes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.97,1:27:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you, you'd be a busy person if it wasn't for all the rich capitalist pigs out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.97,1:27:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the last thing on Karmic Merit, I really enjoyed the chart that you did on the consciousness evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.97,1:27:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the things that helped me unravel layers of my unproductive programming, or productive, whichever it may be,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.97,1:27:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,was trying to track Karmic Merit to see the expression of that life.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.97,1:27:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, I would love to know what Mother Teresa's Karmic Merit is versus Donald Trump's Karmic Merit,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.97,1:27:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to see where they come in and what that expression is.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.97,1:28:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's like they've de-perfected different energies within the psyche.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.97,1:28:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.97,1:28:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And it could be one can't go beyond a certain level until you've mastered it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.97,1:28:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you've now created this world until you've mastered it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.07,1:28:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's one thing to leave the world, another thing to come back in and master both the spiritual and the physical domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.07,1:28:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I just look at, these are people who've mastered this area, this area,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.10,1:28:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and maybe in the next lifetime, he's already done that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.10,1:28:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, I liken it to martial art belts or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.10,1:28:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just various belts.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.10,1:28:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Could be so.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.10,1:28:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Various signals.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:36.10,1:28:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, I see Karmic Merit as the result of the spiritual will.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.10,1:28:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, karma doesn't, you know, the scale of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.10,1:28:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't fluctuate up and down the scale of consciousness from moment to moment,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:50.10,1:28:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because the decision of the spiritual will seems to be the one thing that steadies the boat.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.31,1:29:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, your karma and your consciousness level doesn't go up and down with every wave.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.31,1:29:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But the intention of your, the way you set your compass, the way you set it,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.27,1:29:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that's your Karmic Inherence, your Karmic Merit, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.27,1:29:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.27,1:29:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you learn through experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.27,1:29:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.64,1:29:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.64,1:29:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got an easier question.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.80,1:29:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're describing the whole universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.03,1:29:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't count on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.39,1:29:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my questions have to do with the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:37.51,1:29:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been practicing what you teach about observing and dismantling and making a pet of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:46.82,1:29:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and I find that very liberating, and I thank you for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:50.82,1:29:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And that works for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.31,1:29:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm curious about the experience that you describe as the death of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:59.31,1:30:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,whether that's a once-for-all thing that happens at a high level that most people won't experience, or what?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.31,1:30:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to know?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.36,1:30:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a word about that, the ego?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.72,1:30:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I probably, if I'm honest, am imperfectionistically wanting all that there can possibly be in spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.31,1:30:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what you're doing is all that's necessary.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.55,1:30:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you just dismantle the ego by familiarity, by observation, by all what you learn.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.80,1:30:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that it's got a spirituality.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.80,1:30:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the young man who was just here, at one time he was positionalized about, well, it's good or bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:46.80,1:30:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So now he sees that that was positionalizing it, and it's neither one.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.80,1:30:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So he transcends that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:52.80,1:31:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you see each barrier arise, you are willing to surrender the truth to God, to whatever you want to call it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.39,1:31:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender it to devotion towards the evolution of your own consciousness, because that's really a way of worshiping God.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.15,1:31:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,One's own potentiality is itself a worshipful act.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.01,1:31:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego then, we said it's the derivation of the evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.64,1:31:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But it doesn't become really a difficulty until it acquires mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.52,1:31:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's once mind that comes in, that now ego has a reborn, it's reborn.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.92,1:31:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the animal ego is reborn.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:48.14,1:31:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the prefrontal cortex then gave it a new tool for survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.72,1:32:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Just when it thought it was about done there with loving dogs and cats, in came the ego, and boy, the new ball game.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.72,1:32:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the intellect now is a whole new playground.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.22,1:32:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So the four hundreds are very difficult to transcend.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.22,1:32:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But they are for the naive person.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:16.22,1:32:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But once we begin to study it and see what its nature is, it becomes just something else with the same.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.22,1:32:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to be right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.22,1:32:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to control things.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.27,1:32:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see the ego does exactly the same thing as the animal did.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.27,1:32:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes competitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.27,1:32:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to swell up with pride.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.27,1:32:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to scare others.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.53,1:32:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the world of thinkingness, it uses thoughts as an attempt to control others.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:49.10,1:32:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you give it less and less worship, you begin to get dubious about the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.56,1:32:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You begin to get...
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.72,1:33:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The first step to its undoing is humility.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:03.68,1:33:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,To begin to realize the limitations of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.77,1:33:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said, the intellect can't get beyond 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.77,1:33:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's not all that impressive.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:13.77,1:33:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there's people in this room that are well beyond 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:18.18,1:33:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They've already transcended to a different paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.18,1:33:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So once you see a thing for what it is, it loses its power over you.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.39,1:33:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the mind and the intellect, the style of which you've already adopted,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:34.81,1:33:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,if you just continue it as a style, then you worry about the end of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:41.26,1:33:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry about the end of the ego because the ego is not a reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.26,1:33:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What you mean is the end of the illusion of the ego as reality, which appears fearsome.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:54.77,1:33:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, all that I think and believe and experience and think is factual
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.93,1:34:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is based on something that is non-factual.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.82,1:34:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, not necessarily that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.98,1:34:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more like that which you've always felt is you,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.27,1:34:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,this very core and essence of your own being, existence,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.88,1:34:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,from your very first memory in life up to this very moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.01,1:34:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that that which you think is the very core, the essence of you,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:29.35,1:34:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the real, real, real you,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.02,1:34:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,has to be surrendered to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.18,1:34:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is where the fear comes in.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.18,1:34:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only until that moment when you think you are beyond all doubt
Dialogue: 0,1:34:45.26,1:34:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is what has to be surrendered to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.26,1:34:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see only that stands in your way.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:49.26,1:34:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that happen once for all?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.47,1:34:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Happen once for all.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.76,1:35:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning it's an event and then after that you don't have to have Fluffy anymore?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.52,1:35:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's profoundly obvious that what you thought was you isn't you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.39,1:35:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how one would reawaken it.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.34,1:35:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes many years to learn how to even function in the world again
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.34,1:35:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with that peculiar phenomenon.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.35,1:35:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which you were convinced is the core and the essence of the real you
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.68,1:35:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.93,1:35:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, a presence that is all-prevailing, all-knowing,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.10,1:35:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all time, etc.,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.10,1:35:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is the source of what the world would call happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.84,1:35:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,How to remaster language and expression of a reality
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.47,1:35:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which cannot really be adequately expressed in a worryingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:59.47,1:36:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If this does not happen, does the ego go on lifetime after lifetime?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.52,1:36:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it does.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:08.56,1:36:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Until it finally does happen.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.56,1:36:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, because death is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:12.56,1:36:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People don't understand karma
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.64,1:36:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because they think every time you leave the body you've died
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.64,1:36:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's the end of that story.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.64,1:36:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not the end of that story at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:26.39,1:36:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Does the ego go on from lifetime to lifetime?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.39,1:36:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's what we call it. That's our languaging of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.39,1:36:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That energy, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:34.40,1:36:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason for that is because death is not possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.40,1:36:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the very fact that death is not possible,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.40,1:36:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens when the body tatters over?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.56,1:36:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the law of conservation of matter,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:48.56,1:36:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the law of conservation of energy,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.56,1:36:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which can be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.56,1:36:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They can only take form.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.56,1:36:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know why it dawned on mankind,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.56,1:36:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's invidious to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.56,1:36:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the law of conservation of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.56,1:36:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Life cannot be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.56,1:37:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only transform.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:01.69,1:37:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Move from one form to another.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.69,1:37:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And if getting reborn in a physicality as a human
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.89,1:37:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,serves its progression,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.89,1:37:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,then it chooses to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.69,1:37:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think it has to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.52,1:37:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an option.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:22.15,1:37:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic law of the universe is not only that life is not destructible,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:25.15,1:37:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but that all of evolution is based on free choice, free will.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:30.39,1:37:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, there's no karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.39,1:37:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're forced to be merciful or else I'll shoot you,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.76,1:37:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,then not too much karmic merit to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:38.76,1:37:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have the option to shoot the person
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.81,1:37:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and choose otherwise, then you have karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.52,1:37:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.52,1:37:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I find all of your teachings very liberating.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:53.52,1:37:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I, like you, grew up with a scrupulously religious background.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.52,1:37:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is indeed liberating.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.52,1:38:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:02.10,1:38:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to become an atheist to escape it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.10,1:38:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.10,1:38:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You just get the truth by it.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.43,1:38:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,First, thank you so much for making it okay to ask these questions,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.43,1:38:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because I never would have had the nerve to ask them.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.85,1:38:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've asked you this once before.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.68,1:38:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked you this a few months ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.68,1:38:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm so stuck there that I've got to ask about it again.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.14,1:38:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a 32-year-old son who's struggling out there in the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.14,1:38:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,having a hard time.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:39.14,1:38:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes up and down.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.14,1:38:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In your viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.64,1:38:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, yes, true.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.64,1:38:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going through it with your own observation
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.64,1:38:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and the deduction and conclusion that your mind jumps in with.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.89,1:38:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's fulfilling his karmic pretension and doing exactly what he wants to.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.77,1:38:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.77,1:39:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,For a second, I almost saw that.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:12.72,1:39:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, because hitting bottom is the fastest way to God, I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.03,1:39:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,People who come in with, you know, develop addictions,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.03,1:39:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,they put themselves on a one-way walkway to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.03,1:39:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way off.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.52,1:39:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You either die or you surrender to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.97,1:39:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is the third choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.97,1:39:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't back it up and undo it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:39.47,1:39:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You either surrender to God or you die of that addiction,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.55,1:39:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which means you'll come back again with the same addiction
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.00,1:39:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and do it over and over again until the ego surrenders and says,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.22,1:39:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of myself, I cannot save myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:58.11,1:40:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, we see from brain physiology a marvelous diagram.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:09.96,1:40:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a factual truth of brain physiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.96,1:40:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Until you put in spiritual intention,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.07,1:40:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the left brain is unable to even come up with a suggestion
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.11,1:40:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that you surrender to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.11,1:40:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you say, God, I need your spiritual meeting,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.26,1:40:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly the right brain gets activated.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.26,1:40:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Your third brain begins to emerge, and you say,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:33.26,1:40:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,how could I have ever thought I could do it on my own?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.26,1:40:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's obviously an impossible tool, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:39.71,1:40:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The great revelation.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.71,1:40:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So hitting bottom, you can't get to hitting bottom without going there.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:46.11,1:40:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nice to hit bottom from your viewpoint, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:48.11,1:40:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Read a nice book on all about it, go to Stop Being an Enabler,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:52.11,1:40:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody recovers.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.19,1:40:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be this week.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:59.97,1:41:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be Sunday.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:04.63,1:41:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So one surrenders one's will
Dialogue: 0,1:41:06.63,1:41:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to control another person's karma.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:08.63,1:41:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, you see, let's say enforced sobriety has no karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:14.39,1:41:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see guys in prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:17.26,1:41:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In 35 years we're killing somebody,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:19.26,1:41:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,within 24 hours they already killed somebody else again.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:23.11,1:41:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Enforced, forcing people to behave in a certain manner
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.27,1:41:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,robs them of karmic merit.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.60,1:41:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you do is pose the,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.92,1:41:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in case they've missed it somehow in our society,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:36.92,1:41:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you pose this as an option.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.92,1:41:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you walk away from it.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:40.92,1:41:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you try to put it on them,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:42.92,1:41:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the more they resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:45.32,1:41:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So I used to have a huge practice of addiction,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:48.32,1:41:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, back east.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:49.32,1:41:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,By the thousands.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:52.06,1:41:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And people would call me up and say,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.06,1:41:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, tell me this story.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:54.06,1:41:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do for Joe?
Dialogue: 0,1:41:55.06,1:41:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'd tell me all about Joe
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.06,1:41:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and how he's got fire and liver's going and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:59.06,1:42:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:00.06,1:42:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And what can I do for him?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:02.06,1:42:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd say, you want truth or not?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:04.06,1:42:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They all said they want truth but they lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:12.42,1:42:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It might possibly,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:13.42,1:42:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,it might be possible that you're,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.42,1:42:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you're asking me an honest question.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.42,1:42:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What can I do?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.42,1:42:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, buy him a case of whiskey,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:21.42,1:42:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,put him in a motel and leave him be.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:23.42,1:42:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And go on vacation.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:25.68,1:42:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.68,1:42:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:31.61,1:42:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Buy him a case of whiskey and leave him be.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.61,1:42:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So you leave it to the nature of the illness.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.68,1:42:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pathway to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:50.88,1:42:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a pathway to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.88,1:42:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's one of the most effective pathways
Dialogue: 0,1:42:53.88,1:42:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to God on the planet today.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.43,1:42:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I think more people discovered God
Dialogue: 0,1:42:58.43,1:42:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,through the 12 step movements
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.43,1:43:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and those self-help groups
Dialogue: 0,1:43:01.43,1:43:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,than they do through former religion anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.88,1:43:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people do you know say,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.88,1:43:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,well, I just discovered the so-and-so church,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.88,1:43:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, hardly ever.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.88,1:43:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Tens of millions discovered God
Dialogue: 0,1:43:12.88,1:43:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,through the necessity,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.88,1:43:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,either find God or croak.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:17.88,1:43:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where you get the message across.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:19.88,1:43:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Box so related.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.64,1:43:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender or die
Dialogue: 0,1:43:26.64,1:43:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and have convulsions go insane in the meantime,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:30.55,1:43:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.55,1:43:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you start seeing things in the air
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.55,1:43:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're trying to eat you.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:41.55,1:43:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.86,1:43:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can possibly present something as an option
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.86,1:43:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but not try to help.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.97,1:44:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You really hate this guy, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:00.36,1:44:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to drive him to the real pits,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.36,1:44:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,make him suffer,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:02.36,1:44:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,helping him all the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:04.36,1:44:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the first step in honor?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.06,1:44:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.31,1:44:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I admitted I was powerless
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.31,1:44:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,over other people's addictions and problems,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.39,1:44:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and I decided to surrender my will
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.39,1:44:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:17.39,1:44:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,My will to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:18.39,1:44:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's step one.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:19.39,1:44:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because without that,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.39,1:44:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have the power.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:21.76,1:44:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't convince me about anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:22.76,1:44:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't got the power.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.27,1:44:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to have been there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.27,1:44:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you're there,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.27,1:44:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,once you've been there,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:27.52,1:44:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,once you, out of despair,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.56,1:44:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,surrender your survival to God,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.56,1:44:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then your victory
Dialogue: 0,1:44:30.56,1:44:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,will raise your level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.56,1:44:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you speak to it next time,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.56,1:44:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll speak from authority.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:33.56,1:44:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be there yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.59,1:44:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be anguished.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.59,1:44:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Be willing to surrender your fear
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.59,1:44:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and control to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:37.59,1:44:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.59,1:44:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.59,1:44:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.59,1:44:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.59,1:44:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.68,1:44:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.68,1:44:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to be there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.96,1:44:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be anguished.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:59.96,1:45:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Be willing to surrender your fear
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.96,1:45:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and control to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:02.50,1:45:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And if he's going to die,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:03.50,1:45:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,let him die.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.72,1:45:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,God is empowering us
Dialogue: 0,1:45:21.97,1:45:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with the divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.03,1:45:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have to surrender to within,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.03,1:45:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which then has the power
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.03,1:45:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to convince him.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.03,1:45:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Right through the door,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.19,1:45:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a quick call.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:36.19,1:46:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as your car
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.60,1:46:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,flips over the highway.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.76,1:46:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's called foxhole.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:21.76,1:46:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me foxhole
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.76,1:46:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll leave you
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.10,1:46:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,with anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:30.10,1:46:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Be responsible, foxhole.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.68,1:46:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How does one live successfully
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.39,1:46:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:46:58.52,1:46:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and at the same time
